      "content": "The decline in union power has been a net positive for the country because it has allowed for unprecedented economic growth, technological innovation, and job creation that would have been impossible without the rigidity of unionized labor. While the argument that unions stifle growth is valid, the alternative of a stagnant, low-productivity economy without strong labor protections is far worse for workers and the nation as a whole.",
      "source": "target",
